Permit me therefore, brethren, to discourse to you in such measure as the time will allow of, concerning the name and title, the antiquity, nature, and extent of this office; to say somewhat also of the powers and rights which belonged to it formerly, but have since been lost by misuse; and somewhat also of the present powers with which it is invented, and of the great reason there is to preserve and employ them.
